fields.name: 3-devices, 12-month subscription
fields.description: This is our Community product for individuals or small businesses and organisations operating locally. It includes the address data for one local authority of your choosing and allows up to 3 devices to use the app concurrently. Larger organisations may also want to use this option to check the app for suitability before scaling up to extra devices and / or address data. It includes online support only. Please note that if this package is enough for your needs, then it must be renewed every 12 months but will continue to remain free. Please note that failure to renew will result in your data being deleted 1 month after the renewal expiry data. You will be sent regular emails warning of you this before your data is deleted. The maximum data storage for this option is 200Mb.

fields.name: 12-devices, 6-month subscription
fields.description: This product allows up to 12 devices to login and use the app concurrently. The subscription is for 6 months  It includes the address data for 5 local authorities of your choosing. Includes online and 24/7 telephone support. The maximum data storage for this option is 1Gb.

fields.name: 12-devices, 12-month subscription
fields.description: This product allows up to 12 devices to login and use the app concurrently. The subscription is for 12 months  It includes the address data for 5 local authorities of your choosing. Includes online and 24/7 telephone support. The maximum data storage for this option is 1Gb.

fields.name: Address data load for United Kingdom
fields.description: Automatically loads the address data for the entire United Kingdom into your account's database. Includes all door numbers, street numbers, ward names and post codes for the selected local authority areas. These can then be allocated to Rounds for your own delivery, canvassing or surveying needs. Your existing data will be exported to a file, before the new data is loaded into your account's database on our system, should you wish to revert back to it for any reason.

fields.name: South Tyneside Green Party
fields.description: South Tyneside Green Party (STGP) is a federal party of the Green Party of England and Wales (GPEW). It covers the borough of South Tyneside, within Tyne & Wear, Northeast England. The borough has contains the two Parliamentary Constituencies of Jarrow and South Shields. Its monthly meetings are held in South Shields, where it currently has one councillor, David Francis, for Beacon & Bents ward.
fields.image_caption: Election of first South Tyneside Councillor in May 2019.

fields.name: South Shields Campaign Group
fields.description: South Shields Campaign Group is a sub-group of South Tyneside Green Party. It campaigns in the Parliamentary Constituency of South Shields at both national and local election levels.

fields.name: Belgrave Terrace
fields.comments:
Residences on left hand side of street only, from Beach Road. Leave St Thomas Complex Residential Home, as this is included in a special round. Property number 2 is split into two flats: 2 (lower) and 2a (upper). 

Do not deliver or call at number 6 as staunch Labour supporters.

Parking restrictions: None, but avoid parking in this street as parking is difficult due to high volume of visitors to residential home.

fields.name: Broughton Road
fields.comments: Do not include St Paul and St John's Church Centre near junction with Anderson Street.

fields.name: Flagg Court
fields.comments: This is a small estate in it's own right, spread out over several pathways. It also includes a health centre and parade of shops. No deliveries or canvassing is required for the latter.

fields.name: Barnes Road
fields.comments: Do not call at Number 7 as strict Lib-Dem supporter. All even door numbers on this street.

fields.name: Ocean Road
fields.comments: Mainly restaurants on this street (on right hand-side, heading towards beach) but some residential properties above restaurants. Largely residential on left-hand side. Door numbers start at 4, as numbers 1 to 3 were demolished years ago and not replaced.
Green Party supporters. Call back later with window poster.
